ERROR #1 - MongoDB Connection: SSL TLS Alert Internal Error
================================================================================

Observed behavior:
- npm start failed with:
  MongooseServerSelectionError: Could not connect to any servers in your MongoDB Atlas cluster.
  SSL error: tlsv1 alert internal error

Root cause:
- Current IP address was NOT whitelisted in MongoDB Atlas Network Access.
- Atlas rejects connections at TLS handshake if IP is not in whitelist.

Solution:
1. Go to MongoDB Atlas dashboard → Network Access
2. Add your current IP address (or 0.0.0.0/0 for development)
3. Remove redundant tls: true option from mongoose.connect()

Result after fix:
- Successfully connected to MongoDB Atlas

