ERROR #7 - deleteEvent: Cast to ObjectId Failed for Empty String
================================================================================

Observed behavior:
- GraphQL mutation deleteEvent returned error:
  "Cast to ObjectId failed for value \"\" (type string) at path \"_id\" for model \"Event\""
  path: ["deleteEvent"]

Root cause:
- Empty string "" was passed as eventId parameter
- Mongoose tried to cast "" to ObjectId but failed
- No validation in deleteEvent resolver to check if eventId is empty before querying

Solution:
1. Added validation to check if args.eventId is empty or whitespace-only
2. Throw UserInputError with clear message if ID is missing
3. Also improved return: now properly populates creator and returns events as objects

Result after fix:
- Empty eventId now returns: "Event ID is required and cannot be empty."
- deleteEvent returns all remaining events with properly populated creator data

