ERROR #9 - Restart shows Exit Code 143 (looks like failure)
================================================================================

Observed behavior:
- Terminal often shows command exit code 143 during restart flow.
- It can look like server startup failed.

Root cause:
- Exit code 143 means process received SIGTERM (15).
- During restart, this is expected when you run kill/pkill to stop old server processes.
- If the old process is terminated first, shell may report 143 even though the next start works.

How to read it correctly:
- If you see both lines below after restart, server is healthy:
   Connected to MongoDB
   Server ready at http://localhost:4000/graphql

- If you see EADDRINUSE, another process is still using port 4000.

Safe restart command:
1. pkill -f "nodemon index.js"
2. pkill -f "node index.js"
3. sleep 1
4. npm start
5. lsof -nP -iTCP:4000 -sTCP:LISTEN

Result:
- Exit code 143 during restart is usually normal process termination, not an application code error.
